A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 State Government – Equal Access to Public Services for Individuals With
3 Limited English Proficiency and Individuals With Disabilities
4 FOR the purpose of altering provisions of law relating to equal access to public services for
5 individuals with limited English proficiency to include individuals with disabilities;
6 establishing certain requirements for equal access to public services for certain State
7 departments, agencies, or programs, including developing a language access plan for
8 certain individuals; requiring the Governor’s Office of Immigrant Affairs to oversee,
9 monitor, investigate, and enforce certain provisions of law; requiring certain State
10 departments, agencies, and programs to implement certain provisions of law on or
11 before certain dates; and generally relating to equal access to public services for
12 individuals with limited English proficiency and individuals with disabilities.
